	<h4>Puppy Worms</h4>
	
	<p>Yes, puppies do have worms sometimes!  We deworm the dogs the minute they enter foster care.  However, one deworming may not be enough.  Some websites suggest that 90% of puppies have some form of worm.  Additionally, a second or third deworming is often needed to kill off the hatched eggs that the first deworming did not eliminate.  If you see worms within the first week or two of bringing home your new puppy, <a href="/contact">please contact us!</a>  </p>
	
